Liverpool defender, Trent Alexander-Arnold has welcomed Borussia Dortmund winger, Jadon Sancho to Anfield. Alexander-Arnold, who is a close friend to Sancho, wants the 20-year-old to make a transfer move to join Jurgen Klopp’s side. DAILY POST had reported that Liverpool, alongside Man United and Chelsea are also interested in signing Sancho from Dortmund this summer. “If he [Jadon Sancho] comes to Liverpool, he would make our team better,” Alexander-Arnold told Michael Dapaah on Instagram live. “So I would be more than happy for him to come. “I played with him for England, and he is a special, special, special, special talent.” Sancho has been impressive for Dortmund since he joined the Bundesliga giants from Manchester City in 2017.